post.summary:
`POST /api/v1/commands/apply-layout` — apply a **stored** layout to the
running multiview, live, at the next frame boundary (role: write;
per-object authz; 202) — ADR-W019, invariant #11 Class-1.

`POST /api/v1/routing/{kind}/take` — take (apply) a crosspoint (role: write;
per-destination authz; Idempotency-Key). `200 {class, applied}` for a hot
Class-1/Reset-lite re-point; `202 {operation_id}` for a Class-2 migration.

AlarmRecordDoc.description:
`OpenAPI` mirror of [`multiview_core::alarm::AlarmRecord`].

Serde-equivalent field-for-field. `id` is the alarm id string;
`raised_at`/`dwell` are media-time nanoseconds.
